AIM:
Deploy an HTML webpage using a Dockerfile and share it on Docker Hub.

--------------------------------------------------
index.html
--------------------------------------------------

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Docker Web Page</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello from Docker!</h1>
</body>
</html>

--------------------------------------------------
Dockerfile
--------------------------------------------------

FROM nginx:latest

COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

EXPOSE 80

--------------------------------------------------
Build Docker Image
--------------------------------------------------

docker build -t html-webpage .

--------------------------------------------------
Run Docker Container
--------------------------------------------------

docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name webpage-container html-webpage

--------------------------------------------------
Verify Webpage
--------------------------------------------------

Open Browser:

http://localhost:8080

--------------------------------------------------
Login to Docker Hub
--------------------------------------------------

docker login

--------------------------------------------------
Tag Docker Image
--------------------------------------------------

docker tag html-webpage YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/html-webpage:v1

--------------------------------------------------
Push Image to Docker Hub
--------------------------------------------------

docker push YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/html-webpage:v1

--------------------------------------------------
Verify Image on Docker Hub
--------------------------------------------------

docker pull YOUR_DOCKERHUB_USERNAME/html-webpage:v1

--------------------------------------------------
RESULT
--------------------------------------------------

Successfully deployed an HTML webpage using a Dockerfile, created a Docker image, ran it as a container, and shared the image on Docker Hub.
